3-30-2011

Lists the direct PDF link next to each search result in PubMed, using API of http://thepaperlink.appspot.com and http://paperlink2.appspot.com

It enhances the existing results display by showing: 
* Impact Factor of the Journal 
* Direct link to its PDF file 
* External page of the article 
* Faculty 1000 score and comment page link
* "Peaks", which is based on Impact Factor (the playground for "Peaks" is at http://paperlink2.appspot.com/static/peaks.html)
* ...


For Firefox (not work in 4.0 yet), please use the following:
* http://userscripts.org/scripts/show/97865
* https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/thepaperlinkforpubmed/

For Safari, please use the following:
* http://thepaperlink.appspot.com/static/thepaperlink.safariextz

For Mobile Devices, please try our mobile site:
* http://thepaperlink.appspot.com/m (or visit http://thepaperlink.com on your mobile device)


There is one more thing, we just released the js client for "the Paper Link".
* http://thepaperlink.appspot.com/js/ (shorten URL http://goo.gl/m5C49)
* instruction for the js client is at http://en.dogeno.us/?p=7567


Change Log:
* v0.1.1 - first public version
* v0.1.2 - "bookmark all" for users of "pubmeder at appspot.com"
* v0.2.0 - two-hit for fast data fetching
* v0.2.1 - bug fix
* v0.2.2 - add https support
* v0.2.3 - test using "Peaks" api
* v0.2.4 - option page ui improved, "Peaks" full functional